{{\pard\plain \s2\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs28\kerning28\cgrid 
Application Programming Interfaces (APIs)
\par}
{\tc\tcl2 \v Application Programming Interfaces (APIs)}
SeaBreeze provides two distinct interfaces to control spectrometers. You are free to use and extend either interface, but note that most new development and support from Ocean Optics will focus on the newer {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADU" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeAPI}}} interface, in preference to the older legacy {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAJK" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeWrapper}}} interface.\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s120\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec }\ls1\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
SeaBreeze 2.0: {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADU" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeAPI}}} (C++ class) or {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADT" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeAPI.h}}} (C functions)\par
\pard\plain \s120\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec }\ls1\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
SeaBreeze 1.0: {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAJK" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeWrapper}}} (C++ class) or {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAAJJ" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeWrapper.h}}} (C functions)\par}
\par
Note that detailed documentation for the C++ methods can be found in the corresponding C functions.\par
Regrettably, at writing the {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADU" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeAPI}}} (2.0) can only be used from a full SeaBreeze source distribution. Its headers are not designed in such a way that {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAAADU" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 SeaBreezeAPI}}} can be called without access to the full SeaBreeze include tree, which currently is not provided through the binary installers.\par}
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABDL}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABDL}
{{\pard\plain \s2\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs28\kerning28\cgrid 
Distribution Contents
\par}
{\tc\tcl2 \v Distribution Contents}
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid     SeaBreeze/       The driver and key components\par
        doc/         Documentation relating to SeaBreeze and its API\par
        include/     headers for building SeaBreeze\par
          api/       exportable headers for client applications\par
        os-support/  helpers for specific operating systems\par
          linux/     provides udev rules allowing non-root users to claim devices\par
          windows/   provides working Visual Studio 2005, 2010 and 2012 solutions\par
        src/         core SeaBreeze source for all operating systems\par
        test/        command-line tests, including seabreeze-util cmd-line utility\par
        sample-code/ "recipes" demonstrating how to call SeaBreeze for common tasks\par
    daemons/         server daemons layered atop SeaBreeze for remote / concurrent access\par
    util/            miscellaneous programs related to spectroscopy which may or may not \par
                     require SeaBreeze\par
}
\par}
