{{\pard\plain \s2\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs28\kerning28\cgrid 
Generated Documentation
\par}
{\tc\tcl2 \v Generated Documentation}
SeaBreeze documentation is now maintained in Doxygen format, and can be rendered as HTML, RTF (MS Word), Unix 'man' pages, or other styles. For convenience, pre-rendered documentation is generated for each customer release (RTF, converted to Microsoft .docx) which may be found in the ./doc directory.\par
Assuming you have the "doxygen" command installed (available free at {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "http://doxygen.org" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 http://doxygen.org}}}
 \'96 optionally with GraphViz for UML), you can generate documentation automatically in HTML, RTF, and 'man' formats by typing:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid     $ make doc\par
}
\par
Open doc/html/index.html in a browser (or rtf/refman.rtf in Word) to navigate the results. Note that RTF fields won't self-populate until you "Select All" then "Update Fields" (F9).\par}
