{\tc\tcl4 \v Cygwin}
The following should work on most Cygwin environments, assuming Visual Studio is installed: {
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid     $ cd seabreeze\par
    $ export VISUALSTUDIO_PROJ=VisualStudio2010    (or 2005 or 2012)\par
    $ make\par
}
\par
Note that this is simply using the Cygwin bash shell and GNU toolchain (make) for automation; the actual compiler invoked is Visual Studio. At this time, we have not found a way to support native Cygwin GCC or MinGW (submissions/solutions welcome!)\par}
