{{\pard\plain \s4\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\fs20\cgrid 
Common Build or Runtime Errors
\par}
{\tc\tcl4 \v Common Build or Runtime Errors}
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid Error: NativeUSBWinUSB.c(26): fatal error C1083: Cannot open include file: 'Winusb.h'\par
Fix:   add os-support\\windows\\WinDDK_Includes to your configuration's include path\par
       (SeaBreeze->References->Configuration Properties->VC++ Directories->Include)\par
\par
Error: fatal error LNK1104: cannot open file 'winusb.lib'\par
Fix:   Add C:\\WinDDK\\nnn\\lib\\$(OS)\\$(ARCH) to your configuration's "Library Directories"\par
       (same process as above).\par
\par
Error: fatal error C1083: Cannot open include file: 'api/SeaBreezeWrapper.h' (etc)\par
Fix:   add seabreeze\\include to your configuration's include path with\par
       (Solution 'SeaBreeze' -> Project 'SeaBreeze' -> Properties -> Configuration\par
        Properties -> C/C++ -> General -> "Additional Include Directories")\par
\par
Error: Cannot open .sln file\par
Fix:   Our sources are normally built and tested using Microsoft Visual Studio\par
       2010. If you require support for other compilers, please let us know and we\par
       will endeavor to provide appropriate configuration files.\par
       \par
Error: LINK : fatal error LNK1123: failure during conversion to COFF: file invalid or corrupt\par
Fix:   Uninstall .NET 4.5.1 and re-install .NET 4.0\par
       (cf http://stackoverflow.com/questions/10888391, 6626397, etc)\par
\par
Error: Runtime: An unhandled exception of type 'System.BadImageFormatException' occured in CSharpDemo.exe\par
Fix:   This nearly always means that SeaBreeze.dll was compiled in 32-bit mode and linked to \par
       a 64-bit CSharpDemo.exe, or vice-versa.  Please ensure that both the library and client \par
       application are compiled to the same target and try again.\par
}
\par}
\par}
