\par}
{\tc\tcl2 \v Installing SeaBreeze}
{
\par
\pard\plain \s120\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec }\ls1\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDW" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Windows}}}\par
\pard\plain \s120\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec }\ls1\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDX" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 Linux}}}\par
\pard\plain \s120\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pndec }\ls1\adjustright \fs20\cgrid 
{\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK  \\l "AAAAAAABDY" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 MacOS}}}\par}
\par
{\bkmkstart AAAAAAABDW}
{\bkmkend AAAAAAABDW}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
Windows
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v Windows}
Simply double-click SeaBreeze-vX.Y-Setup32.msi (or *64.msi), which should install:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid     SeaBreeze.dll  -> C:\\Windows\\System32\par
    *.INF          -> C:\\Program Files\\Ocean Optics\\SeaBreeze\\Drivers\par
    *.h            -> C:\\Program Files\\Ocean Optics\\SeaBreeze\\API\par
    *.lib          -> C:\\Program Files\\Ocean Optics\\SeaBreeze\\Library\par
}
\par
Note that the driver installation process won't be complete until you physically insert an Ocean Optics spectrometer into your computer's USB port. At that time, the New Hardware Wizard should pop-up and ask how you would like to locate an appropriate device driver. The recommended process is:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab Insert spectrometer into available USB port\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
2.\tab Wait for New Hardware Wizard to come up\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
3.\tab On "Can Windows connect to Windows Update...?" select "No, not this time"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
4.\tab On "What do you want the wizard to do?" select "Install from a list or specific location (Advanced)"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
5.\tab Click "Search for the best driver in these locations."\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
6.\tab Uncheck "Search removable media"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
7.\tab Click "Include this location in the search:"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
8.\tab Browse to "C:\\Program Files\\Ocean Optics\\SeaBreeze\\Drivers"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
9.\tab Click Next\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
10.\tab Click Finish\par}
\par
If the New Hardware Wizard doesn't come up on its own, you can use the following procedure instead:\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
1.\tab From the Start Menu, right-click on Computer, then select "Manage"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
2.\tab Select the Device Manager\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
3.\tab Select "Ocean Optics Spectrometers"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
4.\tab Right-click on the desired spectrometer and select "Update Driver"\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
5.\tab Select "Browse my computer" (not "Search automatically")\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
6.\tab Ensure "include subfolders" is checked\par
\pard\plain \s140\fi-360\li360\widctlpar\fs20\cgrid 
7.\tab Browse to C:/Program Files/Ocean Optics/SeaBreeze/Drivers and click "Okay"\par}
\par
You will know that the drivers have been installed correctly if the Device Manager adds the string "(WinUSB)" at the end of the spectrometer name.\par
Finally, you can "pre-load" the drivers using Microsoft's {\field {\*\fldinst { HYPERLINK "http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/hardware/ff544775%28v=vs.85%29.aspx" }{}}{\fldrslt {\cs37\ul\cf2 dpinst.exe}}} utility (included), where $ARCH is i386 or amd64 as appropriate (see 'dpinst /?' for other options):\par
{
\par
\pard\plain \s40\li0\widctlpar\adjustright \shading1000\cbpat8 \f2\fs16\cgrid   C:> cd /Program Files/Ocean Optics/SeaBreeze/Drivers\par
  C:> $ARCH/dpinst.exe /q /lm /c\par
}
\par}
