{\bkmkend AAAAAAABDX}
{{\pard\plain \s3\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid 
Linux
\par}
{\tc\tcl3 \v Linux}
For Linux computers to recognize Ocean Optics spectrometers and allow non-root users to claim and control the devices, you'll need to install the provided "10-oceanoptics.rules" file, found under os-support/linux, copying it to (usually) /etc/udev/rules.d. Note that older versions of udev use the "SYSFS" rule nomenclature; the provided file uses the newer "ATTR" standard.\par}
