{\s17\sa60\sb30\widctlpar\qj \fs22\cgrid 
This provides a unique ID of each device that is detected or specified. The IDs are copied into the user-provided buffer. These IDs are weak references: attempting to access a device that no longer exists will cause an error value to be returned but should not cause any instability. The IDs may be entirely random, but a given ID will always refer to the same device for as long as the program is running. This will return the number of device IDs actually copied into the array or 0 on error. \par
}}
